<subSubSection pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
Prothorax. Pronotum with complete carina at lateral edge (Fig. 141), reaching from hind angle to anterior edge of prothorax. Pterothorax. Scutellum with middle of anterior edge broadly concave. Also. Tarsal claws with both basal and apical points on each side, without basal setae; bursa copulatrix with proximal sclerites bilobed (Fig. 142). Diagnosis is based on type species. 
<taxonomicName authority="Motschoulsky, 1859" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Platynychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platynychus fuscipennis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipennis">Platynychus fuscipennis</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="CandÃ¨ze">Candeze</normalizedToken>
, 1860, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Motschoulsky, 1859" authorityName="Motschoulsky" authorityYear="1859" class="Insecta" family="Elateridae" genus="Platynychus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Platynychus incostatus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="incostatus">Platynychus incostatus</taxonomicName>
Fleutiaux, 1931 have lateral carina of pronotum reaching only 9/10 to anterior edge of pronotum, and scutellum mesally notched. Known from PR China, and Southeast Asia, 4 spp.
</paragraph>
